I just turned 40 and already have had two close friends my age be diagnosed with breast cancer (and both battled hard and beat it!) My friend Diana had no symptoms and didn’t have anything show up on her regular screening but on a whim decided to do a more advanced screening because she was told she had dense breast tissue and that’s when they found her cancer. I know like 98% of my followers are men but y’all have sisters or girlfriends or wives so tell them to get screened. Save the titties 🙌🏻 I know @suzesuzeq would be proud 🦋 #breastcancerawareness #mamogram #cancerscreening #breastcancer #savethetitties

One of the cooler moments of my entire mma journey. I was backstage at the fights and a producer said “hey someone wants to meet you”…I don’t get star struck easily, but I went full fan girl mode when @realroyce popped around the corner. I couldn’t believe he knew who I was let alone that I fought and am a brown belt. He said “let’s do a face off pic” …and as cheesy as this sounds, it gave me chills to stare into the eyes of the man who helped create this sport and who’s fingerprints are still everywhere today. His life’s work has impacted all of us who live, eat and breathe the UFC and that was not lost on me in this moment. It was really special. Oss 🙏🏻 #roycegracie #mma #ufc #bjj #graciebjj #thefirst #ufc283

If you watched the ESPN + post show you saw me go off about this scorecard. Here (link in bio) I discuss in depth why. Y’all know that I’m usually the one sticking up for the judges when many of the fans are crying robbery…not this time. And for good reason. That scorecard combined with the fact that the ref who had the most egregious and dangerous mistake I’ve ever seen in mma the night before for Fury FC was allowed to judge the UFC the next day shows a complete lack of accountability on the part of the Texas Commission. It’s important to talk about this stuff. Even though the right person won the main event and even though the Fury fighter survived (though not without injury) we have to talk about these things loudly enough for change to happen.
Words of wisdom 🐮

A very successful couple of days in New York spending time with our team that will be working towards listing Alta in the coming months.

Access to capital markets will be hugely important as Alta scales to rapidly drive increased participation in martial arts and combat sports, the world over.

Connecting MMA’s 600 million plus global fan base for training experiences with amazing coaches and gyms across the planet is Alta’s mission. So if you run a martial arts academy/combat sports gym, get in contact and allow us help you grow your revenues and members!

Training martial arts is the BEST solution for physical and mental health in the world, so go to @trainalta to get started!

What a weekend in NYC with @coach_kavanagh and @nick.langton visiting with the team that will be working towards listing @trainalta in the coming months! 

What does that mean? Having access to capital markets will allow @trainalta to much more quickly become THE destination for those of us who want to take our UFC passion from watching on our couches to LIVING THAT LIFE. And for the tens of thousands of martial arts gym owners across the U.S. and beyond it means passive revenue so they can focus on doing what they do best…teaching! 

So much more to come!

Claudia’s time on earth is ending and she is being called home to be with the Lord. She is my best friend’s mom whom I have known all my life. She was diagnosed with Alzheimer’s in her late 50s and it has been a difficult journey for her and her family to navigate since. The grief of these last few days is, in many ways, second hand for me. She’s not my mom …but I love her daughter so so much. Summer lost her dad to cancer when we were teenagers. Grief is not new to her. But despite all that she has lost in an earthly sense, she is the embodiment of this song. If you ask her how she has handled losing both her parents to hideous slow moving diseases…she will still speak of the goodness of God. It is her father’s legacy, her mother’s legacy and it will be her legacy one day as well…that so many were introduced to God’s love and mercy through them ❤️…love you @say284 . #alzheimers #alzheimersawarenessmonth #alzheimersassociation #alzheimersdisease #godsloveneverfails #goodnessofgod
